<div class="legal-page guide-page">
  <h1>❓ Frequently Asked Questions: Your Meme Explorer Answers</h1>
  
  <section class="hero-section">
    <p class="tagline">Comprehensive answers to common questions about features, troubleshooting, and getting the most from our platform</p>
    <p class="meta"><strong>Last Updated:</strong> July 13, 2026 | <strong>Reading Time:</strong> 12 minutes | <strong>By:</strong> Meme Explorer Support Team</p>
  </section>

  <p class="intro">Quick answers to the most common questions we receive. Can't find your answer? <a href="/contact">Contact our support team</a> for personalized help.</p>

  <h2>Getting Started</h2>

  <h3>Q: Do I need an account to browse memes?</h3>
  <p><strong>A:</strong> No! You can browse our curated feed without creating an account. However, accounts unlock personalization, collections, gamification, and syncing across devices. We recommend creating one to get the full experience. It's free and takes 30 seconds.</p>

  <h3>Q: How does the quality system work?</h3>
  <p><strong>A:</strong> We use a six-stage pipeline evaluating technical quality, engagement metrics, content safety, visual standards, user feedback, and novelty. Only the top 5% of Reddit memes make it to your feed. See our <a href="/guides/quality_system">quality system guide</a> for the complete technical breakdown.</p>

  <h3>Q: Where does content come from?</h3>
  <p><strong>A:</strong> We curate content from over 30 top-tier meme subreddits including r/memes, r/dankmemes, r/wholesomememes, r/me_irl, and many more. All content respects Reddit's terms of service and credits original posters.</p>

  <h2>Personalization & Recommendations</h2>

  <h3>Q: How long does personalization take to work?</h3>
  <p><strong>A:</strong> The system needs 7 days of regular interaction to build accurate preferences. You'll notice improvements within 2-3 days, but week two is when personalization really shines. Users report 300% better relevance by day 7. Be patient and engage authentically for best results.</p>

  <h3>Q: Can I reset my taste profile?</h3>
  <p><strong>A:</strong> Yes! Visit Settings → Privacy → Reset Personalization Profile. This clears your taste data while preserving saved memes and account details. Use this if your preferences have fundamentally changed or if multiple users shared your account. Warning: This action is permanent and restarts the 7-day training period.</p>

  <h3>Q: Why am I seeing memes I've already viewed?</h3>
  <p><strong>A:</strong> Our 24-hour deduplication window prevents same-day repeats, but memes may reappear after 24 hours, especially highly-engaging content. If you're experiencing excessive repetition, it may indicate you've viewed most available content in your categories. Try <a href="/guides/discovery">discovery mode</a> to explore new areas.</p>

  <h3>Q: How do I tell the algorithm I dislike certain content?</h3>
  <p><strong>A:</strong> Skip content quickly by scrolling past or using skip buttons. Consistent skipping patterns teach the algorithm your dislikes. The system learns from negative signals as effectively as likes—active skipping helps more than passive scrolling.</p>

  <h2>Collections & Organization</h2>

  <h3>Q: How many collections can I create?</h3>
  <p><strong>A:</strong> Unlimited! Power users maintain 20-50 themed collections. We recommend starting with 5-10 to avoid overwhelming organization. See our <a href="/guides/collections">collections guide</a> for organizational strategies.</p>

  <h3>Q: Can I share my collections with friends?</h3>
  <p><strong>A:</strong> Yes! Each collection has a shareable link. Recipients can view your collection and add memes to their own collections. Collections marked "private" require login to access. Public collections are shareable with anyone.</p>

  <h3>Q: Is there a limit to saved memes?</h3>
  <p><strong>A:</strong> No hard limits. However, we recommend curating actively—keeping only true favorites. Collections with 1,000+ memes become difficult to navigate. Quality over quantity creates more useful collections.</p>

  <h3>Q: How do I bulk organize saved memes?</h3>
  <p><strong>A:</strong> Visit your Saved page and use the "Organize" mode. Select multiple memes, then move them to collections in batch. Power users dedicate 10 minutes weekly to collection maintenance for optimal organization.</p>

  <h2>Gamification & Progression</h2>

  <h3>Q: What do XP and levels actually do?</h3>
  <p><strong>A:</strong> XP tracks engagement and unlocks achievements, titles, and leaderboard positions. Higher levels grant access to beta features and exclusive content first. While primarily for fun, gamification increases engagement by 3x according to our data. Learn the complete system in our <a href="/guides/gamification">gamification guide</a>.</p>

  <h3>Q: What happens if I break my daily streak?</h3>
  <p><strong>A:</strong> Streaks reset to zero if you miss a day. However, reaching certain milestones (7, 30, 100 days) earns permanent badges even after breaks. We recommend streak freezes for planned absences—earn them through achievements or occasional promotions.</p>

  <h3>Q: How do I climb the leaderboard?</h3>
  <p><strong>A:</strong> Leaderboards rank by XP across different timeframes (daily, weekly, all-time). Consistent engagement beats sporadic intensity—daily streaks, thoughtful curation, and community participation maximize XP. Top users typically maintain 50-100 day streaks with active collection management.</p>

  <h2>Technical Issues</h2>

  <h3>Q: Images aren't loading. What should I do?</h3>
  <p><strong>A:</strong> First, check your internet connection. If connected, try these steps: (1) Refresh the page, (2) Clear browser cache, (3) Try a different browser, (4) Disable browser extensions temporarily. If problems persist, Reddit or Imgur may be experiencing outages—check their status pages or contact <a href="/contact">our support</a>.</p>

  <h3>Q: The site feels slow. How can I speed it up?</h3>
  <p><strong>A:</strong> Performance tips: (1) Close unused browser tabs, (2) Disable unnecessary extensions, (3) Clear cache periodically, (4) Use modern browsers (Chrome, Firefox, Safari), (5) Check your internet speed. Mobile users: Use Wi-Fi when available for optimal performance.</p>

  <h3>Q: My saved memes disappeared. Can I recover them?</h3>
  <p><strong>A:</strong> Saved memes sync across devices via your account. If missing: (1) Confirm you're logged into correct account, (2) Refresh the page, (3) Check if accidentally moved to different collection. If genuinely lost, <a href="/contact">contact support</a> immediately—we maintain backups and can usually recover within 30 days.</p>

  <h3>Q: Why can't I like or save memes?</h3>
  <p><strong>A:</strong> This typically indicates you're not logged in or session expired. Log in again to restore functionality. If problem persists while logged in, clear cookies and cache, then log in fresh. Still having issues? Report to <a href="/contact">support</a> with browser details.</p>

  <h2>Mobile & Cross-Platform</h2>

  <h3>Q: Is there a mobile app?</h3>
  <p><strong>A:</strong> We currently offer a mobile-optimized website that works excellently on phones and tablets. A dedicated app is in development for 2027. Bookmark our site to your home screen for app-like experience.</p>

  <h3>Q: Do my saved memes sync between devices?</h3>
  <p><strong>A:</strong> Yes! Everything syncs automatically when logged in—saved memes, collections, preferences, XP, and streaks. Use any device seamlessly. Note: Personalization may adapt slightly to device context (mobile vs desktop) to optimize for screen size and usage patterns.</p>

  <h3>Q: Can I use keyboard shortcuts?</h3>
  <p><strong>A:</strong> Yes! On desktop: Arrow keys navigate, Spacebar scrolls, L likes, S saves, R opens random meme, Cmd/Ctrl+K opens search. See <a href="/guides/best_practices">best practices guide</a> for complete shortcut list.</p>

  <h2>Privacy & Data</h2>

  <h3>Q: What data do you collect?</h3>
  <p><strong>A:</strong> We collect interaction data (likes, saves, views) to power personalization, basic account info (email, username), and anonymous analytics. We never sell data, share personal info with third parties, or track you outside our platform. Read our <a href="/privacy">privacy policy</a> for details.</p>

  <h3>Q: Can I export my data?</h3>
  <p><strong>A:</strong> Absolutely. Visit Settings → Privacy → Export Data to download complete interaction history, saved memes, collections, and account details. Exports provided in JSON format within 24 hours.</p>

  <h3>Q: How do I delete my account?</h3>
  <p><strong>A:</strong> Settings → Account → Delete Account. This permanently removes all data including saved memes, collections, and XP. Action is irreversible after 30-day grace period. We recommend exporting data first if you might want records.</p>

  <h2>Content & Moderation</h2>

  <h3>Q: How do I report inappropriate content?</h3>
  <p><strong>A:</strong> Click the report flag on any meme, select reason, and submit. Our team reviews reports within 24 hours. Repeated false reports may result in account restrictions. We take content quality seriously and appreciate legitimate reports.</p>

  <h3>Q: Why was my favorite meme removed?</h3>
  <p><strong>A:</strong> Memes may be removed if: (1) Original poster deleted from Reddit, (2) Copyright claim received, (3) Violates content policy, (4) Broken image link. We don't remove arbitrarily—each removal has specific cause.</p>

  <h3>Q: Can I submit my own memes?</h3>
  <p><strong>A:</strong> We currently curate from Reddit only. To get your memes featured, post to relevant subreddits with quality content. If it gains traction and passes our quality pipeline, it'll appear automatically. We're exploring direct submissions for future development.</p>

  <h2>Discovery & Exploration</h2>

  <h3>Q: How does Random Mode work?</h3>
  <p><strong>A:</strong> Random Mode shows quality content outside your typical preferences, not truly random selection. It identifies what you usually like, then shows opposite spectrum content while maintaining quality standards. Great for breaking filter bubbles and discovering new interests. Full details in our <a href="/guides/discovery">discovery guide</a>.</p>

  <h3>Q: Why do I keep seeing the same format?</h3>
  <p><strong>A:</strong> This indicates strong format preference in your taste profile. To diversify: (1) Actively skip that format occasionally, (2) Like different formats when you encounter them, (3) Use Random Mode to explore alternatives, (4) Browse by format category to deliberately expose yourself to variety.</p>

  <h2>Account & Billing</h2>

  <h3>Q: Is Meme Explorer free?</h3>
  <p><strong>A:</strong> Yes! All core features are completely free. We monetize through non-intrusive advertising that respects your experience. We're exploring optional premium features for future, but core meme browsing will always remain free.</p>

  <h3>Q: How do I change my username or email?</h3>
  <p><strong>A:</strong> Settings → Account → Edit Profile. Username changes allowed once every 90 days. Email changes require verification at new address. Previous usernames remain reserved to prevent impersonation.</p>

  <h3>Q: I forgot my password. What now?</h3>
  <p><strong>A:</strong> Click "Forgot Password" on login page. Enter your email for reset link (check spam folder). Links expire after 24 hours for security. No email access? <a href="/contact">Contact support</a> with account details for recovery assistance.</p>

  <h2>Features & Customization</h2>

  <h3>Q: Can I filter out certain subreddits?</h3>
  <p><strong>A:</strong> Yes! Settings → Content Preferences → Excluded Subreddits. Add communities you want to avoid. Personalization respects these exclusions permanently. Use this for content types that consistently don't resonate.</p>

  <h3>Q: Is there a dark mode?</h3>
  <p><strong>A:</strong> Yes! Settings → Appearance → Dark Mode, or use the sun/moon icon in navigation. Dark mode syncs across devices and respects system preferences by default. Perfect for late-night browsing.</p>

  <h3>Q: How do I disable notifications?</h3>
  <p><strong>A:</strong> Settings → Notifications → Disable All, or customize by type (streak reminders, achievement unlocks, etc.). We respect notification preferences and never spam. Unsubscribe links included in all emails.</p>

